article.description: Cathy Joens' 14 second-half points helped hold off an Oklahoma rally in the first round.
article.headline: Joens' 22 points leads George Washington
article.linkText: Big second half leads George Washington past OU
article.story:
NORMAN, Okla. (AP) -- Maria Villarroel scored 17 points and
Dionnah Jackson added 13 as Oklahoma beat Sparta Praha 94-56 in
exhibition play Thursday night.

Villarroel grabbed four rebounds and had an assist and Jackson
had five rebounds and five assists for the No. 21 Sooners, who also
got 10 points each from Caton Hill and Leah Rush.

Oklahoma led 58-26 at intermission, after shooting 57 percent to
Sparta Praha's 30 percent in the first half.

The Sooners also outrebounded Sparta Praha 53-36.

Jana Vokrinkova paced Sparta Praha with 14 points, including
three 3-pointers. She added five rebounds and two assists.
